cs.NE, cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.COM
Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a novel application of deep reinforcement learning in Internet congestion control. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also a likely category as the paper deals with congestion control, which is a core networking task. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper uses deep network policies to capture intricate patterns in data traffic and network conditions. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper proposes a new approach to solving a real-world problem using AI techniques. 
- cs.COM (Computers and Society) is a less likely category, but it could be relevant as the paper discusses challenges facing the real-world adoption of RL-based congestion control, such as fairness and safety.
